    "body": "### Problem\n\nI am not sure if it is relevant, but `~/.local/state/nvim/log` records the following after nvim reads stdin:\n\n```\nWRN 2025-06-10T19:21:12.484 ui.842976  tui_handle_term_mode:240: TUI: terminal mode 69 detected, state 2\nWRN 2025-06-10T19:21:12.484 ui.842976  tui_handle_term_mode:230: TUI: terminal mode 2026 unavailable, state 4\nWRN 2025-06-10T19:21:12.484 ui.842976  tui_handle_term_mode:230: TUI: terminal mode 2027 unavailable, state 0\nWRN 2025-06-10T19:21:12.484 ui.842976  tui_handle_term_mode:230: TUI: terminal mode 2031 unavailable, state 0\nWRN 2025-06-10T19:21:12.484 ui.842976  tui_handle_term_mode:230: TUI: terminal mode 2048 unavailable, state 4\nERR 2025-06-10T19:21:12.846 nvim.842977.0 os_set_cloexec:501: Failed to get flags on descriptor 3: Bad file descriptor\n```\n\nThen I try to `:restart`, and nvim hangs.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean - < /dev/null`\n2. `:restart`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nnvim does not hang, or `:qall`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-93925fe\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNOME Terminal 3.56.2 using VTE 0.80.2 +BIDI +GNUTLS +ICU +SYSTEMD\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
